author: Corey Anderson
title: Hey, Minnesota: here are your 2015 WNBA champion Lynx
text:
By Corey Anderson | 03:56 pm MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Center Sylvia Fowles holding the championship trophy. 
The October chill didn't stop thousands from assembling on Hennepin Avenue in Minneapolis Friday morning to honor the 2015 WNBA World Champion Minnesota Lynx. MinnPost contributing photographer Mike Dvorak was on hand to capture the festivities. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Forty-five degrees is still t-shirt weather in Minnesota. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Guards Anna Cruz and Lindsay Whalen take a selfie mid-parade. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Head Coach Cheryl Reeve waving to the crowd along Hennepin Avenue. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Guard Renee Montgomery showing off the 2015 championship trophy. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak The Minnesota Lynx mascot, Prowl, doing her job to get the crowd pumped. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Guard Seimone Augustus and forward Maya Moore holding the 2011 and 2013 championship trophies. MinnPost photo by Mike Dvorak Fans young and old enjoyed seeing their 2015 WNBA Champs.
